title: Liberty High sweeps Freedom, has a perfect Thursday of athletics
text:
View/Post Comments 
Lehighvalleylive put the Liberty-Freedom rivalry in the spotlight on Thursday night, covering the field hockey and soccer tripleheader at Bethlehem Area School District Stadium. 
The Hurricanes ruled the evening, earning close victories over their rivals in all three sports and improving to 3-1 in the battle for the Liberty-Freedom bell. 
As it turns out, the sweep of Freedom was part of a dominant day of athletics for Liberty as the football and girls volleyball teams also posted victories.
